{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"435c278d-4072-46de-88f0-42c4f68c2652","content":"","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01FsmnyzXcEh2yNtgaYPvtGG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Providing NativeAOT crash dump config"},"type":"function"}],"interactionId":"96b05220-27f4-4688-86c1-62d0e11aac43","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to configure automatic crash dump collection for a NativeAOT .NET 11 app running in Kubernetes. They have `createdump` installed at `/opt/tools/createdump`. Let me provide the necessary environment variables and pod spec changes.\n\nFor .NET NativeAOT crash dump collection, the key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` - enables automatic crash dump generation\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` - full dump (MiniDumpWithFullMemory) or other types\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` - path/pattern for the dump file\n\n\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpDiagnostics=1` - optional, for additional diagnostics\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, crash dump support varies by .NET version, with .NET 8+ providing more robust support through `createdump`.\n\nThe key environment variables are:\n- `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` to enable dumps\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` to control dump size (1=Normal, 2=With Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\n- `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` for the dump file path pattern\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpPath` pointing to the `createdump` binary location\n\nFor Kubernetes deployments, I need to account for environment variables on the container, a volume mount for storing the dumps, and potentially adjusting the security context since `createdump` requires `SYS_PTRACE` capability to function properly.","outputTokens":585,"requestId":"D825:1C33BD:5FD81C9:67BBCBC:69FBEFE1"},"id":"03bcfd8b-3e63-45aa-ab5f-9a1478120ac7","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:50:41.168Z","parentId":"cb7bbc72-bae1-4449-aec5-60310c508e9d"}
