{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f963b234-fe83-406a-ac3f-3dd977dcedbe","content":"Here's what you need:\n\n**Environment variables** for your container:\n\n| Variable | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` | `1` | Enables automatic dump on crash |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType` | `4` | Full dump (1=Normal, 2=WithHeap, 3=Triage, 4=Full) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | `/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t` | Dump path (`%p`=PID, `%t`=timestamp) |\n| `DOTNET_CreateDumpPath` | `/opt/tools/createdump` | Custom createdump location (required for NativeAOT) |\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n  - name: my-app\n    env:\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n      value: \"1\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n      value: \"4\"\n    - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n      value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\"\n    - name: DOTNET_CreateDumpPath\n      value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"\n    securityContext:\n      capabilities:\n        add:\n        - SYS_PTRACE          # required — createdump uses ptrace\n    volumeMounts:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n  - name: crash-dumps\n    emptyDir:\n      sizeLimit: 2Gi          # tune to your expected dump size\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `SYS_PTRACE` is **mandatory** — `createdump` uses `ptrace()` to snapshot the process.\n- `DOTNET_CreateDumpPath` is required because NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump` — it won't find it without this.\n- Use `emptyDir` for ephemeral collection; swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Adjust `DbgMiniDumpType` to `2` (WithHeap) for smaller dumps if full dumps are too large.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"96b05220-27f4-4688-86c1-62d0e11aac43","outputTokens":569,"requestId":"D80C:165916:5CBB700:64AD1DE:69FBEFF0"},"id":"ef980d1f-789e-48bf-99d7-9c2a75be59fd","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:50:51.614Z","parentId":"46cba1e1-11bb-470a-812c-ba6454770f9b"}
